newsitem.title: TAIWAN: Taiwan money rates end sharply lower.
newsitem.headline: Taiwan money rates end sharply lower.

text.p: Taiwan's short-term money rates closed sharply lower on Friday as banks sought to liquidate excess funds before the end of the current monthly reserve period on November 3, dealers said.
The overnight interbank rate ended at 5.019 percent against Wednesday's 5.267 close, with 30-day commercial paper at 5.00-5.10 against 5.15-5.20. The market was closed on Thursday.
Dealers said they expected rates to remain at current levels in the near term.
The bond market saw no transaction in afternoon trade.
